      "nodeLabel": "J1"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774966923614",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# 2.3 Convergence Properties\r\n\r\naddition is random var: $Y = \\pm  1/\\sqrt{n}$\r\n\r\nit's expectation: $E[Y] = 1/2 \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} - 1/2 \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}}$ = 0\r\n\r\nvariation: $Var(Y) = E[(Y - E[Y])^2] = E[Y^2]$ \r\n\r\n$E[Y^2] = 1/n$ as prob. that we see Y^2 is always 1\r\n\r\nNow for this \r\n$$\r\n\r\nW_n\\left(\\frac{i}{n}\\right) = W_n\\left(\\frac{i-1}{n}\\right) + \\frac{X_i}{\\sqrt{n}}, \\quad \\text{for all } i \\geq 1\r\n\\tag{sc01.f.1.1}\r\n\r\n$$\r\n\r\n",
      "x": 1201,
      "y": 1004,
      "width": 532,
      "height": 211,
      "nodeLabel": "N1"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774967027103",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# What's $E[W_n(1)]$  (here 1 means i=n) ?\r\n\r\n$E[W_n(1)] = E[W_n((n-1)/n)] + 0 = E[W_n((n-2)/n) + 0] + 0 = ... = E[W_n(1/n)] = E[X_1/\\sqrt{n}] = E[Y] = 0$ \r\n",
      "x": 1837,
      "y": 1063,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 93,
      "nodeLabel": "N2"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774967125889",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# 2. What's $Var[W_n(1)]$ ?\r\n\r\n$$\r\nVar[W_n(1)] = Var(W_n(\\frac{n-1}{n}) + Y) = Var(W_n(\\frac{n-1}{n})) + 2 Cov(W_n(\\frac{n-1}{n}), Y) + Var(Y) = Var(W_n(\\frac{n-1}{n})) + 1/n = ... = 1/n + 1/n + ... = n \\cdot 1/n = 1 \r\n\r\n$$",
      "x": 1837,
      "y": 1281,
      "width": 948,
      "height": 98,
      "nodeLabel": "N3"
    }
  ],
